A Mpumalanga family went for days believing that their relative was recovering well at a hospital in Delmas, only to find her decomposed body in the morgue a week later. The Simelane family from Botleng township has told of their trauma which saw them view several bodies as they were searching for their relative, Deliwe Simelane, 57, who they took to the notorious Bernice Samuel Hospital on April 25. Speaking to Sowetan  on Wednesday, Simelane's niece Dudu Simelane said her aunt was first admitted to the facility  early in April, when she was treated for chronic high blood pressure and diabetes. To read the full story, please visit SowetanLIVE.